            "text": "(Colorado Sun) — “Colorado oil and gas regulators looking to avoid a rash of abandoned and unplugged oil and gas wells are proposing to increase financial guarantees by operators for each of their wells — a price tag that could add up to billions of dollars. The draft financial assurance regulations, released by the Colorado Oil and Gas Conservation Commission, cover all 50,000 oil and gas wells in the state and in general require a full-cost of plugging financial guarantee of $78,000 for each of a company’s wells.”",
